'''Timothy Michael Ream''' (born October 5, 1987) is an American professional [[Association football|soccer]] <!--Do not change to "football". Wikipedia articles are written in the style of English most associated with the subject, and as Ream is American, please use American English --> player who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|center-back]] or [[Defender (association football)|left-back]] for [[Major League Soccer]] club [[Charlotte FC]] and [[Captain (association football)|captains]] the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States national team]].

==Youth and college soccer==
Born in [[St. Louis]], Missouri,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fulhamfc.com/player-profiles/tim-ream |title=Tim Ream |publisher=Fulham F.C. |access-date=February 27, 2020 |archive-date=February 27, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227154056/https://www.fulhamfc.com/player-profiles/tim-ream |url-status=live }}</ref> Ream was a 2005 NSCAA All-Midwest Region selection with his high school, [[St. Dominic High School (O'Fallon, Missouri)|St. Dominic]], and after finishing his career with 15 goals and a school-record 39 assists, was tabbed All-State, All-Conference and Class 2 Defensive Player of the Year in both 2004 and 2005, was a St. Louis Post-Dispatch All-Metro selection and garnered Archdiocesan Athletic Association Player of the Year honors following senior season. He helped lead St. Dominic to the 2004 Missouri Class 2 state title. Ream also played with academy club [[St. Louis Scott Gallagher Soccer Club|St. Louis Scott Gallagher]], winning national championships in 2003 and 2004.{{citation needed|date=February 2020}}

Ream attended [[Saint Louis University (United States)|Saint Louis University]] where he was a regular figure as a defender for the [[Saint Louis Billikens]], earning NSCAA first-team All-Region and second-team All-Conference honors. During his college years Ream also played for [[Chicago Fire Premier]] in the [[USL Premier Development League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uslsoccer.com/teams/13381239/22315-13381307/10355035.html |title=United Soccer Leagues (USL) |publisher=Uslsoccer.com |access-date=January 26, 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120711123416/http://www.uslsoccer.com/teams/13381239/22315-13381307/10355035.html |archive-date=July 11, 2012}}</ref>

==Professional career ==
===New York Red Bulls===
{{Quote_box|
 width=40%
|align=right
|quote="He has a future. I probably shouldn't say too much, but Ream has a chance to be a national team player. He's a center back who is comfortable and calm in possession of the ball. He plays a good passing game, he's an excellent passer. A European-type center back who, I think, reminds me of Rio Ferdinand in the Premier League. Ream is strong tactically and never stressed, and of course he's good in the air. He has a top-class attitude and spirit."
|source= -Red Bulls coach [[Hans Backe]] speaking about Tim Ream, March 17, 2010 <ref>{{cite news |url=http://goal.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/03/17/red-bulls-coach-likes-one-young-defender-in-particular/ |work=The New York Times |first=Jack |last=Bell |title=Red Bulls Coach Likes One Young Defender in Particular |date=March 17, 2010 |access-date=March 17, 2010 |archive-date=March 23, 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100323150844/http://goal.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/03/17/red-bulls-coach-likes-one-young-defender-in-particular/ |url-status=live }}</ref>
|}}

Ream was drafted in the second round (18th overall) of the [[2010 MLS SuperDraft]] by [[New York Red Bulls]].<ref>[http://web.mlsnet.com/mls/events/superdraft/2010/draft_tracker.jsp 2010 MLS SuperDraft] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100117173019/http://web.mlsnet.com/mls/events/superdraft/2010/draft_tracker.jsp |date=January 17, 2010 }}</ref>  His play during pre-season impressed many observers, including new coach Hans Backe who was pleased with his distribution and tactical awareness.{{citation needed|date=February 2020}}

On March 20, 2010, Ream started and played the full 90 minutes for Red Bulls in a 3–1 victory against [[Santos FC]], which was the first match played at the new [[Red Bull Arena (Harrison)|Red Bull Arena]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bigapplesoccer.com/article.php?article_id=22956 |title=THE STARTING XI Salou, Kandji partner up top |publisher=Bigapplesoccer.com |date=March 20, 2010 |access-date=January 26, 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029201611/http://www.bigapplesoccer.com/article.php?article_id=22956 |archive-date=October 29, 2013}}</ref> He made his professional debut on March 27, 2010, playing the full 90 in New York's opening game of the [[2010 Major League Soccer season|2010 MLS season]] against [[Chicago Fire Soccer Club|Chicago Fire]] that ended in a 1–0 victory for New York.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/gamecast?id=289679&cc=5901&league=USA.1 |title=Gamecast: New York Red Bulls v Chicago – Major League Soccer – ESPN Soccernet |publisher=[[ESPN]] |date=March 27, 2010 |access-date=January 26, 2012 |archive-date=September 27, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110927135620/http://soccernet.espn.go.com/gamecast?id=289679&cc=5901&league=USA.1 |url-status=dead }}</ref> On September 11, 2010, he scored his first professional goal (and MLS goal) against the [[Colorado Rapids]] in a 3–1 win for [[New York Red Bulls]]. Ream ended his first professional season starting all 30 matches for New York and helped New York capture its second regular season [[2010 Major League Soccer|Eastern Conference]] title.<ref>[http://www.mlssoccer.com/matchcenter-recap/red-bulls-beat-revs-clinch-eastern-conference] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101023070503/http://www.mlssoccer.com/matchcenter-recap/red-bulls-beat-revs-clinch-eastern-conference|date=October 23, 2010}}</ref>
Upon the conclusion of the 2010 season, he was named the team's Defender of the Year, and he was one of three listed candidates for [[MLS Rookie of the Year]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.newyorkredbulls.com/post/2010/10/12/new-york-red-bulls-2010-mls-season-awards-contenders |title=New York Red Bulls 2010 MLS Season Awards Contenders |publisher=New York Red Bull Official Website |date=October 12, 2010 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701205837/http://www.newyorkredbulls.com/post/2010/10/12/new-york-red-bulls-2010-mls-season-awards-contenders |archive-date=July 1, 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.newyorkredbulls.com/post/2010/11/19/red-bulls-announce-2010-team-awards |title=Red Bulls announce 2010 team awards |publisher=New York Red Rulls Official Website |date=November 19, 2010 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160322023644/http://www.newyorkredbulls.com/post/2010/11/19/red-bulls-announce-2010-team-awards |archive-date=March 22, 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref>

During Ream's second season in New York, he played and started in 28 of 34 matches during the regular season; he missed 6 matches largely due to international call-ups during the [[2011 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].{{citation needed|date=February 2020}}

In December 2011, during the [[Major League Soccer|MLS]] off-season, Ream spent a short time training with both [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]] and [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]] with permission from the Red Bulls to maintain his fitness during the winter break.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/981575-january-transfer-rumors-tim-ream-scoped-out-by-the-premier-league|title=January Transfer Rumors: Tim Ream Scoped out by the Premier League|first=Mike|last=Daquila|website=Bleacher Report|access-date=August 27, 2020|archive-date=April 11, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210411070009/https://bleacherreport.com/articles/981575-january-transfer-rumors-tim-ream-scoped-out-by-the-premier-league|url-status=live}}</ref> At the beginning of January 2012, Bolton made a transfer offer of £2.5m for him.<ref>{{cite web |author=Trotters move for American |url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/12691/7415635/Bolton-launch-Ream-bid |title=Bolton launch Ream bid &#124; Latest Football Transfer News |website=Sky Sports |date=January 6, 2012 |access-date=January 26, 2012 |archive-date=January 11, 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120111071229/http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/12691/7415635/Bolton-launch-Ream-bid |url-status=live }}</ref> Bolton had recently sold [[Gary Cahill]] to [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], and needed to find a replacement.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fulhamfc.com/players/tim-ream |title=Tim Ream |website=Fulham FC |date=2022 |access-date=September 10, 2022 |archive-date=September 14, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220914082232/https://www.fulhamfc.com/players/tim-ream/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The bid was accepted and after personal terms were agreed he received a work permit on January 24.<ref>{{cite web |author=Holden welcomes arrival of fellow USA international |url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/11672/7452668/Ream-granted-work-permit- |title=Ream 'granted work permit' &#124; Bolton Wanderers News, Fixtures, Results, Transfers |website=Sky Sports |date=January 26, 2012 |access-date=January 26, 2012 |archive-date=November 19, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191119192909/http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/11672/7452668/Ream-granted-work-permit- |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Bolton Wanderers===
[[File:Ream, Tim.jpg|thumb|upright|Ream playing for [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]] in 2015]]

Bolton completed the signing of Ream on January 26, 2012, on a three-and-a-half-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11672/7456386/Ream-completes-Bolton-move|title=Ream completes Bolton move|date=January 26, 2012|website=Sky Sports|access-date=March 22, 2019|archive-date=March 23, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190323072627/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11672/7456386/Ream-completes-Bolton-move|url-status=live}}</ref> He canceled his honeymoon so that he could sign for Bolton.<ref name="ReamHoneymoon">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/honeymoon-cancelled-as-tim-ream-comes-to-boltons-aid-88hm0v6zgv7|title=Honeymoon cancelled as Tim Ream comes to Bolton's aid|first=Ian|last=Whittell|date=January 20, 2012 |access-date=January 31, 2020|via=www.thetimes.co.uk|archive-date=January 26, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126205456/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/honeymoon-cancelled-as-tim-ream-comes-to-boltons-aid-88hm0v6zgv7|url-status=live}}</ref> He was given the number 32 shirt and made his debut for the club in Bolton's 2–0 [[FA Cup]] win at [[Millwall F.C.|Millwall]] on February 18.<ref>{{cite news |title=Millwall 0 – 2 Bolton Wanderers |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/16994618 |website=BBC Sport |date=February 18, 2012 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-date=February 21, 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120221013732/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/16994618 |url-status=live }}</ref> He made his Premier League debut the following weekend in Bolton's 3–0 defeat at [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Chelsea 3 – 0 Bolton Wanderers |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/17082758 |website=BBC Sport |date=February 25, 2012 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-date=January 7, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160107205956/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/17082758 |url-status=live }}</ref> On March 10, 2012, he assisted [[Darren Pratley]]'s opening goal in a 2–1 win over Queens Park Rangers.<ref>{{cite news |title=Bolton Wanderers 2 – 1 Queens Park Rangers |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/17243629 |website=BBC Sport |date=March 10, 2012 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-date=January 31, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190131130852/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/17243629 |url-status=live }}</ref> He went on to appear ten games straight towards the end of the season, but was unable to help the club survive relegation in the [[Premier League]].{{citation needed|date=February 2020}}

For the start of the 2012–13 season, Ream was given the number 5 shirt, previously worn by [[Gary Cahill]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bwfc.co.uk/news/article/squad-numbers-announced-5.6.12-217943.aspx |title=Squad Numbers Announced |publisher=Bolton Wanderers F.C. |date=July 5, 2012 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141227211807/http://www.bwfc.co.uk/news/article/squad-numbers-announced-5.6.12-217943.aspx |archive-date=December 27, 2014 |url-status=live}}</ref> He was given his first start of the 2012–13 season in a 2–0 loss against [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Burnley 2 – 0 Bolton Wanderers |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/19221523 |website=BBC Sport |date=August 18, 2012 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-date=October 23, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181023032643/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/19221523 |url-status=live }}</ref> However, he was sidelined from the first team, due to losing his starting place<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bwfc.co.uk/news/article/glad-to-be-back-22.10.12-439687.aspx |title=Glad To Be Back |publisher=Bolton Wanderers F.C. |date=October 22, 2012 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121024221419/http://www.bwfc.co.uk/news/article/glad-to-be-back-22.10.12-439687.aspx |archive-date=October 24, 2012 |url-status=live}}</ref> and was relegated to the substitutes bench. Despite this, Ream went on to make fifteen appearances.{{citation needed|date=February 2020}}

Ahead of the 2013–14 season, Ream was linked with a move to [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]], a move that was denied by the club and Ream.<ref>{{cite news |title=US star Tim Ream ready to learn new trade with Bolton Wanderers |url=http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/10554989.US_star_Tim_Ream_ready_to_learn_new_trade_with_Bolton_Wanderers/ |publisher=The Bolton News |date=July 18, 2013 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-date=August 26, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160826055600/http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/10554989.US_star_Tim_Ream_ready_to_learn_new_trade_with_Bolton_Wanderers/ |url-status=live }}</ref> After appearing the first three matches as an unused substitute, he started as defensive midfielder for four matches in September.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tim looks for first team spot |url=http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/10634103.Tim_looks_for_first_team_spot/ |publisher=The Bolton News |date=August 26, 2013 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-date=August 26, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160826084807/http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/10634103.Tim_looks_for_first_team_spot/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In early February 2014, he was forced to wear a protective mask in Wanderers games after a collision with [[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|Queens Park Rangers]] striker [[Charlie Austin]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Tim Ream injury sparks defensive dilemma at Bolton Wanderers |url=http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/10969799.Tim_Ream_injury_sparks_defensive_dilemma_at_Bolton_Wanderers/ |publisher=The Bolton News |date=January 29, 2014 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-date=August 26, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160826091626/http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/10969799.Tim_Ream_injury_sparks_defensive_dilemma_at_Bolton_Wanderers/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Throughout the 2013–14 season, Ream played at left back and center back, where he established his partnership with [[Matt Mills]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Dougie Freedman hails Bolton Wanderers standard bearers Matt Mills and Tim Ream |url=http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/10732074.Dougie_Freedman_hails_Bolton_Wanderers_standard_bearers_Matt_Mills_and_Tim_Ream/ |publisher=The Bolton News |date=October 11, 2013 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-date=August 26, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160826091121/http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/10732074.Dougie_Freedman_hails_Bolton_Wanderers_standard_bearers_Matt_Mills_and_Tim_Ream/ |url-status=live }}</ref> and redeemed himself in the first team making 42 appearances. At the end of that season, he was voted the fans' player of the year<ref>{{cite web |title=Tim Ream wins club's Player of the Year award |url=http://www.bwfc.co.uk/news/article/tim-ream-wins-clubs-player-of-the-year-award-1.5.14-1522314.aspx |publisher=bwfc.co.uk |access-date=May 1, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140501235820/http://www.bwfc.co.uk/news/article/tim-ream-wins-clubs-player-of-the-year-award-1.5.14-1522314.aspx |archive-date=May 1, 2014 |url-status=live}}</ref> and the club's player of the year.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tim Ream wins player of the year award at Wanderers |url=http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/sport/11188532.Tim_Ream_wins_player_of_the_year_award_at_Wanderers/ |publisher=The Bolton News |date=May 2, 2014 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-date=June 19, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180619012731/http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/sport/11188532.Tim_Ream_wins_player_of_the_year_award_at_Wanderers/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

Ahead of the 2014–15 season, on July 6, 2014, Ream signed a new three-year contract with Bolton that lasts until the summer of 2017.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sky Bet Championship: Bolton defender Tim Ream signs contract extension |url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/11672/9374061/sky-bet-championship-bolton-defender-tim-ream-signs-contract-extension |website=Sky Sports |date=July 6, 2014 |access-date=July 7, 2014 |archive-date=July 9, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140709031145/http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/11672/9374061/sky-bet-championship-bolton-defender-tim-ream-signs-contract-extension |url-status=live }}</ref> Over the course of the season, he made a total of 44 appearances, missing two matches, one as an unused substitute against Derby County on September 27, 2014<ref>{{cite news |title=Bolton Wanderers 0 – 2 Derby County |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/29289482 |website=BBC Sport |date=September 27, 2014 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-date=December 27, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141227131504/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/29289482 |url-status=live }}</ref> and one through injury.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bwfc.co.uk/news/article/andrew-lonergan-and-tim-ream-cleared-of-serious-injury-2289209.aspx |title=Andrew Lonergan and Tim Ream cleared of serious injury |publisher=Bolton Wanderers F.C. |date=February 23, 2015 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150225174214/http://www.bwfc.co.uk/news/article/andrew-lonergan-and-tim-ream-cleared-of-serious-injury-2289209.aspx |archive-date=February 25, 2015 |url-status=live}}</ref> For a consecutive season, he was named as Bolton's player of the year.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bwfc.co.uk/news/article/tim-ream-named-as-bolton-wanderers-201415-player-of-the-season-2432956.aspx |title=Tim Ream crowned 2014/15 Player of the Season |publisher=Bolton Wanderers F.C. |date=May 1, 2015 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150502162455/http://www.bwfc.co.uk/news/article/tim-ream-named-as-bolton-wanderers-201415-player-of-the-season-2432956.aspx |archive-date=May 2, 2015 |url-status=live}}</ref>

Ahead of the 2015–16 season, Ream was linked with a move to [[EFL Championship|Championship]] rivals [[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|Queens Park Rangers]], who made a bid for him. However, the bid was rejected.<ref>{{cite news |title=Bolton sign Prince-Desir Gouano and reject QPR Tim Ream bid |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/33802910 |website=BBC Sport |date=August 6, 2015 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-date=July 21, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180721045203/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/33802910 |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Fulham===
[[File:Tim ream 2016.jpg|thumb|upright|Ream playing for [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] in 2016]]

On August 20, 2015, Ream was sold to [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]], with whom he signed a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite news |title=American Tim Ream agrees four-year deal with Fulham – sources |url=http://www.espnfc.us/story/2569827/american-tim-ream-agrees-four-year-deal-with-fulham%E2%80%94sources |publisher=ESPN |date=August 20, 2015 |access-date=August 20, 2015 |archive-date=October 29, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191029140323/http://www.espnfc.us/story/2569827/american-tim-ream-agrees-four-year-deal-with-fulham%E2%80%94sources |url-status=live }}</ref> The move had an undisclosed fee and an option to extend his stay by a further year.<ref>{{cite news |title=Fulham have completed the signing of defender Tim Ream on a four-year deal from Bolton Wanderers |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11681/9958233/fulham-have-completed-the-signing-of-defender-tim-ream-on-a-four-year-deal-from-bolton |website=Sky Sports |date=August 20, 2015 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-date=August 15, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160815061303/http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11681/9958233/fulham-have-completed-the-signing-of-defender-tim-ream-on-a-four-year-deal-from-bolton |url-status=live }}</ref>

He made his Fulham debut on August 29, 2015, in a 3–1 win over [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]], playing 90 minutes.<ref>{{cite news |title=Rotherham United 1–3 Fulham |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34024911 |website=BBC Sport |date=August 29, 2015 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-date=March 16, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160316161042/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34024911 |url-status=live }}</ref> He made 29 appearances for the club in his first season, partly due to international commitment<ref>{{cite news |title=Fulham new boy set to miss Huddersfield clash |url=http://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/fulham-new-boy-set-miss-9904679 |publisher=Get West London |date=August 21, 2015 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-date=August 28, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160828184516/http://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/fulham-new-boy-set-miss-9904679 |url-status=live }}</ref> and injuries.<ref>{{cite news |title=Queens Park Rangers v Fulham: Whites missing defender for big derby clash |url=http://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/qpr-v-fulham-whites-missing-10879026 |publisher=Get West London |date=February 12, 2016 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-date=August 28, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160828185332/http://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/qpr-v-fulham-whites-missing-10879026 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=American Exports: Tim Ream nearing return to Fulham lineup after hamstring injury |url=http://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2015/10/23/american-exports-tim-ream-nearing-return-fulham-lineup-after-hamstring-injury |publisher=Major League Soccer Official Website |date=October 23, 2015 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-date=September 24, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160924213435/http://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2015/10/23/american-exports-tim-ream-nearing-return-fulham-lineup-after-hamstring-injury |url-status=live }}</ref> After initially playing as a center back, he was used at left back toward the end of the season, following the departure of [[James Husband (footballer)|James Husband]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Fulham boss weighing up where best to use Tim Ream – with Wolves clash in mind |url=http://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/fulham-boss-weighing-up-best-10720564 |publisher=Get West London |date=January 12, 2016 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-date=August 28, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160828172602/http://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/fulham-boss-weighing-up-best-10720564 |url-status=live }}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club in a 2–1 loss against [[Queens Park Rangers]] on October 1, 2016.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37460403 |title=Fulham 1–2 QPR |website=BBC Sport |date=October 1, 2016 |access-date=October 4, 2016 |archive-date=October 4, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161004113324/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37460403 |url-status=live }}</ref>

Ream scored his first ever Premier League goal for Fulham on [[Boxing Day]] 2022 against [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/dec/26/crystal-palace-fulham-premier-league-match-report|title=Aleksandar Mitrovic seals Fulham win against nine-man Crystal Palace|last=Aarons|first=Ed|website=[[The Guardian]]|date=December 26, 2022 |access-date=December 28, 2022}}</ref>

On October 7, 2023, Ream made his 300th appearance for Fulham in a 3–1 win over Sheffield United.

On December 29, 2023, Ream extended his contract with Fulham until the summer of 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=December 29, 2023 |title=Ream Extends Contract |url=https://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2023/december/29/ream-extends-contract/ |access-date=January 2, 2024 |website= |publisher=Fulham FC |archive-date=January 2, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240102012806/https://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2023/december/29/ream-extends-contract/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Charlotte FC===
On August 7, 2024, Ream signed for Major League Soccer club [[Charlotte FC]] on a two-year contract with the option for a further twelve months.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.charlottefootballclub.com/news/charlotte-fc-signs-u-s-men-s-national-team-defender-tim-ream|title=Charlotte FC Signs U.S. Men's National Team Defender Tim Ream |website=www.charlottefootballclub.com|date=August 7, 2024|accessdate=August 7, 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2024/august/07/ream-leaves-fulham/|title=Ream Leaves Fulham|website=www.fulhamfc.com|date=August 7, 2024|accessdate=August 7, 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:USMNT vs. Trinidad and Tobago (48124967367) (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|Ream with the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] at the [[2019 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].]]

On November 11, 2010, Ream was called up to the [[United States men's national soccer team]] for the first time as part of an 18-man roster for a match against [[South Africa national football team|South Africa]] on November 17 in Cape Town.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ussoccer.com/News/Mens-National-Team/2010/11/Bradley-Names-18-Man-Roster-to-Face-South-Africa-on-Nov-17-in-Cape-Town.aspx |title=Bradley Names 18-Man Roster to Face South Africa on Nov. 17 in Cape Town |publisher=U.S. Soccer |access-date=January 26, 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121003151903/http://www.ussoccer.com/News/Mens-National-Team/2010/11/Bradley-Names-18-Man-Roster-to-Face-South-Africa-on-Nov-17-in-Cape-Town.aspx |archive-date=October 3, 2012}}</ref> He made his international debut that day, starting the match and played until the 67th minute before being replaced by [[Nat Borchers]]. The U.S. won 1–0 with the lone goal coming from fellow [[New York Red Bulls|Red Bull]] teammate [[Juan Agudelo]]. On January 22, 2011, he earned his second international cap against Chile in a 1–1 draw. He played all 90 minutes at center back.{{citation needed|date=February 2020}}

Ream started in their first game of the 2011 Gold Cup, a 2–0 win over [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada]]. He also started the second match against Panama, which the U.S. lost 2–1 for their first ever loss in Gold Cup group play. In the 34th minute, he committed a foul on [[Blas Pérez]] resulting in a penalty kick for Panama. The penalty was converted by [[Gabriel Enrique Gómez|Gabriel Gómez]] and became the match-winner.<ref>{{cite news |title=U.S. FALLS TO PANAMA IN SECOND MATCH OF THE 2011 CONCACAF GOLD CUP |url=http://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2014/03/17/12/57/us-mnt-falls-to-panama-in-gold-cup-group-c-play |publisher=U.S. Soccer |date=June 11, 2011 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-date=August 17, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160817152119/http://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2014/03/17/12/57/us-mnt-falls-to-panama-in-gold-cup-group-c-play |url-status=live }}</ref> In the next match, against Guadeloupe, he was replaced by [[Eric Lichaj]] and did not play in the final four matches of the 2011 Gold Cup.{{citation needed|date=February 2020}}

After a two-year absence, Ream was again called into the U.S. national team in 2013<ref>{{cite news |title=Bolton Wanderers defender Tim Ream called up for USA friendly. His niece of 2 dimensions is named Madison Bretz. Her best friend is named Nadeen Berhil. |url=http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/10607495.Bolton_Wanderers_defender_Tim_Ream_called_up_for_USA_friendly/ |publisher=The Bolton News |date=August 12, 2013 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-date=August 26, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160826115158/http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/10607495.Bolton_Wanderers_defender_Tim_Ream_called_up_for_USA_friendly/ |url-status=live }}</ref> appearing as an unused substitute against [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] on August 14, 2013. On September 3, 2014, he played his first international match in three years, playing 45 minutes in a 1–0 win over [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Czech Republic 0, USA 1 – International Friendly Match Recap |url=http://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2014/09/03/czech-republic-0-usa-1-international-friendly-match-recap |publisher=Major League Soccer Official Website |date=September 3, 2014 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-date=September 24, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160924092819/http://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2014/09/03/czech-republic-0-usa-1-international-friendly-match-recap |url-status=live }}</ref>

Ream also was called up for the [[2015 CONCACAF Gold Cup|2015 Gold Cup]] where he played all 90 minutes against the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]] and helped preserve a 1–0 [[clean sheet]].<ref>{{cite news |title=KLINSMANN CALLS 23 PLAYERS TO DEFEND GOLD CUP TITLE |url=http://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2015/06/23/10/30/150623-mnt-gold-cup-roster-release |publisher=US Soccer |date=June 23, 2015 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-date=June 24, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150624010133/http://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2015/06/23/10/30/150623-mnt-gold-cup-roster-release |url-status=live }}</ref> He scored his first international goal on May 22, 2016, in a friendly against [[Puerto Rico national football team|Puerto Rico]] at the [[Juan Ramón Loubriel Stadium]] in [[Bayamón, Puerto Rico|Bayamón]], [[Puerto Rico]].<ref>{{cite news |title=United States beats Puerto Rico with Tim Ream, Bobby Wood and own goals |url=http://www.espn.co.uk/football/report?gameId=448085 |publisher=ESPN |date=May 22, 2016 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-date=September 14, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160914170443/http://www.espn.co.uk/football/report?gameId=448085 |url-status=live }}</ref>

[[File:Tim Ream WC2022.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Ream playing for the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].]]

On November 9, 2022, Ream was called up for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Who is Tim Ream? Inside the USMNT World Cup Roster |url=https://www.foxsports.com/stories/soccer/usmnt-world-cup-roster-guide-who-is-tim-ream |website=[[Fox Sports]] |access-date=November 11, 2022 |archive-date=November 11, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221111185722/https://www.foxsports.com/stories/soccer/usmnt-world-cup-roster-guide-who-is-tim-ream |url-status=live }}</ref> He started all four games for the U.S. in Qatar, as the U.S. advanced to the Round of 16. He was announced as the U.S. captain of the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=mlssoccer |title=Charlotte FC's Tim Ream named USMNT captain for 2026 World Cup {{!}} MLSSoccer.com |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/charlotte-fc-s-tim-ream-named-usmnt-captain-usmnt-at-world-cup |access-date=2026-05-31 |website=mlssoccer |language=en}}</ref>

==Personal life==
In January 2012, Ream married his childhood sweetheart Kristen Sapienza, who is also a soccer player.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ream keen on Bolton marriage |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11672/7443675/ream-keen-on-bolton-marriage |website=Sky Sports |date=January 20, 2012 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-date=August 15, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160815095156/http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11672/7443675/ream-keen-on-bolton-marriage |url-status=live }}</ref> Twenty-four hours after getting married Ream postponed his honeymoon planned in Tahiti to undergo a move to Bolton Wanderers.<ref name="ReamHoneymoon"/> Ream later stated in [[The Bolton News]] interview that he still made a right choice in postponing his honeymoon.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ream: I still made right choice |url=http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/9690569.Ream__I_still_made_right_choice/ |publisher=The Bolton News |date=May 5, 2012 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |archive-date=August 26, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160826101920/http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/9690569.Ream__I_still_made_right_choice/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

